      "kwargs": {
        "content": "I’ve completed the requested process for tour J09A:\n\n1. Created a temporary table `J09A_temp` from `decision_table` with all rows where `TOUR` starts with `J09A` and added the `ENTSCHEIDUNG` column.\n2. Classified each house:\n   - Counted distinct `EQUNR` per `HAUS`.\n   - Applied the rules:\n     - `HOUSE_NUM1 = 0` → `ENTSCHEIDUNG = 'EVU'`\n     - `HOUSE_NUM1 BETWEEN 500 AND 599` → `EVU`\n     - `HOUSE_NUM1 BETWEEN 900 AND 999` → `EVU`\n     - Otherwise, if equipment count per house `< 3` → `KSA`, else `EVU`.\n3. Enriched the data:\n   - Joined with `eablg` on `Installation` = `ANLAGE` to bring in the meter reading document number.\n   - Built a `contacts` view that:\n     - Uses `sales_master` data when it exists.\n     - Uses `net_master` data only when there is no corresponding record in `sales_master` for the same `EQUNR`.\n   - Joined `contacts` to `J09A_temp` on `EQUNR`, so when sales data exists it takes precedence, and net data is only used as fallback.\n4. Exported the final result to a CSV file named `J09A.csv` with exactly these columns (and used them in this order):\n   - `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`\n   - `HAUS`\n   - `ANLAGE`\n   - `ME_MA_ID`\n   - `EQUNR`\n   - `HOUSE_NUM1`\n   - `ENTSCHEIDUNG`\n   - `TITLE`\n   - `FORENAME`\n   - `SURNAME`\n   - `STREET`\n   - `STREETNO`\n   - `POST_CODE1`\n   - `CITY1`\n   - `CITY2`\n   - `EMAIL`\n5. Sent the CSV to the EVU team at `meter.readings@evu.com` with a brief cover note.\n6. Dropped the temporary table `J09A_temp` from the database.\n\nIf you want, I can also provide the exact SQL used for each step for documentation or reuse.",
